<p>Hmm, they've got the CC license on their site but they need attribution, either to you guys or to us to show who they got the material from.</p>
<p>We would send a DMCA notice to their host to compel them to either take the stuff down or properly attribute that but DMCA is a US law. I believe Korea has its own equivalent law that would allow you to do the same. If they are ignoring you, contact their webhost about it. I'd recommend looking up the proper way to send the notice though, while I send out these notices for stuff on this side finding the right text for a Korean version is beyond my abilities.</p>

