				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hammermaiden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1552358); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1552358&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610180864" alt="HammerMaiden" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1552358)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hammermaiden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1552358); return false;" >HammerMaiden</a></span> <span class="odate time_1386964933 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">13 Dec 2013 20:02</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1914872">
									

<p>Not entirely correct. You can use any character here for anything you'd like to market later. But only if you release that work under the CC/BY/SA 3.0 or compatible license. That means:</p>
<ul>
<li>anyone can reproduce the work in whole or in part for free so long as they credit you.</li>
<li>You credit the SCP wiki and your own work on it as the source of the character</li>
